results.name: Smallest number beginning with 9 that is the product of exactly n distinct primes.
program: (PARI) a(n) = {i = prod(i=1, n, prime(i)); while ((digits(i)[1] != 9) || (omega(i) != n) || (bigomega(i) != n), i++); i;} \\ _Michel Marcus_, Sep 14 2013
results.author: _Ray Chandler_, May 02 2005
